  "text": "Baseline quantitative HBV DNA assessment was performed in all 35 patients from the HBV study group. To evaluate the association between 25(OH)D serum concentration and baseline HBV DNA we used the cut-off value of 10 000 copies/ml [CITATION_1] . In patients with baseline HBV DNA < 10 000 copies/ml (n = 17; 49%) and ≥ 10 000 copies/ml (n = 18; 51%) mean vitamin D concentrations were 18.3 ng/dl and 16.9 ng/dl, respectively. The difference between groups was not statistically significant (p = 0.67). ",
